      "op:rhs": "non-zero class (non-trivial LiftObstruction)",
      "op:verificationDomain": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/Topological"
      },
      "op:verificationPathNote": "TwistedType → non-trivial LiftObstruction at every quantum level",
      "rdfs:comment": "TwistedType obstruction class: the monodromy of a TwistedType contributes a non-zero class to H²(N(C(T')); ℤ/2ℤ) where T' is any QuantumLift of T. TwistedTypes always have non-trivial lift obstructions.",
      "rdfs:label": "MN_7"
    },
    {
