    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_surfaceSymmetry",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/surfaceSymmetry"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Axiomatic derivation of the Surface Symmetry Theorem. Holds at all quantum levels: the composite P∘Π∘G is a well-typed morphism whenever G and P share the same state:Frame. Follows from the definition of the shared-frame condition and the type-equivalence algebra.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_surfaceSymmetry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/CC_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that a CompleteType T satisfies: resolution(x, T) terminates in O(1) for all x ∈ R_n. Follows from IT_7d: when χ(N(C)) = n and all β_k = 0, the resolver has no topological obstructions.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_CC_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/CC_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that the ψ pipeline is monotone: each constraint application cannot increase the fiber deficit. Derived from the definition of the partition refinement order.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_CC_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/CC_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that a CompletenessCertificate implies CompleteType: the certificate attestation is only issued when IT_7d holds, by construction of the CompletenessResolver.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_CC_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/CC_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that the CompletenessAuditTrail witnessCount equals the number of CompletenessWitness records in the trail. Structural invariant of the audit accumulation protocol.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_CC_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/CC_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that the ConstraintNerve nerve computation is deterministic: the same constraint set always produces the same nerve topology. Follows from the nerve functor being a functor (functoriality).",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_CC_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that neg(bnot(x)) = succ(x) in Z/(2^n)Z for all n ≥ 1. Derived symbolically from ring axioms: bnot is bitwise complement, neg is two's complement negation, succ is modular increment. The critical identity in universal form.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that the ring carrier set size is exactly 2^n for all n ≥ 1. Follows from the definition of Z/(2^n)Z.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that Landauer erasure cost scales as n × k_B T ln 2 at quantum level n. Follows from the thermodynamic interpretation: each bit erased from an n-bit ring costs k_B T ln 2.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that the dihedral group D_{2^n} action on Z/(2^n)Z is faithful for all n ≥ 1. The stabilizer of any element is trivial under the full dihedral action.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that canonical form rewriting terminates at all quantum levels. The rewriting system is terminating by lexicographic descent on the term complexity measure.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_6",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_6"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof that the completeness criterion χ(N(C)) = n generalizes to all quantum levels. Derived from the definition of the nerve construction and the Euler characteristic formula for simplicial complexes.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_6"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_7",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QL_7"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Universal proof of the ring topology Euler characteristic identity: χ = 1 − n at quantum level n. Derived from the CW decomposition of the n-dimensional torus formed by the ring's cyclic group action.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QL_7"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_SR_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/SR_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of binding monotonicity: freeCount(B_{i+1}) ≤ freeCount(B_i) for all i in a Session. Follows from the definition of the BindingAccumulator: each appended binding either pins fibers or is a no-op; it never frees them.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_SR_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_SR_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/SR_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that the empty session is the identity element of the session algebra: freeCount(B_0) = total fiber space. The empty accumulator has no pinned fibers by definition.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_SR_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_SR_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/SR_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of session convergence: a session terminates iff freeCount reaches its minimum (the maximum pinned by the given constraint set). Follows from the compactness of the fiber space and monotonicity.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_SR_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_SR_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/SR_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof that disjoint bindings compose without fiber conflict: if two bindings address disjoint fiber sets, their composition is well-defined and their union is also a valid binding.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_SR_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_SR_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/SR_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of contradiction detection correctness: ContradictionBoundary fires iff there exist bindings b, b' in the same Context with the same address, different datum, and same constraint. This is the minimal condition for type contradiction.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_SR_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of nerve realisability: for any target profile with χ* ≤ n and β₀* = 1, there exists a ConstrainedType whose constraint nerve realises the target. Follows from the constructive synthesis algorithm.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of minimal basis bound: the MinimalConstraintBasis for the IT_7d target has size exactly n. Follows from the fiber-by-fiber construction and the minimality criterion.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of synthesis monotonicity: adding a constraint never decreases the Euler characteristic of the constraint nerve. Follows from the nerve inclusion principle.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of synthesis convergence: the TypeSynthesisResolver terminates in at most n steps. Follows from monotonicity (TS_3) and the finite fiber budget bound.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of synthesis-certification duality: a SynthesizedType achieves IT_7d iff the CompletenessResolver certifies it as CompleteType. The duality follows from the shared topological criterion.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_6",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_6"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of Jacobian-guided synthesis efficiency: the Jacobian oracle reduces expected steps from O(n²) to O(n log n). Follows from the information content of the Jacobian at each synthesis step.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_6"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_7",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/TS_7"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of unreachable signatures: β₀ = 0 is unreachable by any non-empty ConstrainedType. Follows from the nerve connectedness of non-empty constraint sets.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_TS_7"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_1"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_6"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of lift unobstructedness criterion: QuantumLift T' is CompleteType iff the spectral sequence collapses at E_2. Follows from the Leray spectral sequence of the quantum level extension.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_2"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_2"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of obstruction localisation: a non-trivial LiftObstruction is localised to a specific fiber at bit position n+1. Follows from the local-to-global structure of the constraint nerve.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_3"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_3"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of monotone lifting: basisSize(T') = basisSize(T) + 1 for trivially obstructed lifts. Follows from the minimal basis construction at Q_{n+1}.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_4"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_4"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of spectral sequence convergence bound: the spectral sequence converges by page E_{d+2} for depth-d configurations. Follows from the filtration length of the constraint nerve chain complex.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_5"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_6"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of universal identity preservation under quantum lifts: every universallyValid identity holds in the lifted ring. Follows from the universal validity definition and ring extension properties.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_6",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"
      ],
      "proof:baseCase": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_6"
      },
      "proof:inductiveStep": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QLS_6"
      },
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/QLS_6"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:validForKAtLeast": 0,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of ψ-pipeline universality for quantum lifts: the ψ-pipeline produces a valid ChainComplex for any QuantumLift. Follows from the functorial construction of the chain complex.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_QLS_6"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of holonomy group containment: HolonomyGroup(T) ≤ D_{2^n}. Follows from the fact that all constraint applications are dihedral group elements.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of additive flatness: additive constraints (ResidueConstraint, DepthConstraint) generate only the identity in D_{2^n}. Follows from the additive structure of the dihedral action.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of dihedral generation: neg and bnot together generate D_{2^n}. Follows from the standard presentation of the dihedral group by involutions.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of holonomy-Betti implication: non-trivial holonomy implies β₁ ≥ 1. Follows from the fact that a non-trivial monodromy requires a topological loop in the constraint nerve.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_5",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_5"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of CompleteType holonomy: IT_7d (β₁ = 0) implies trivial holonomy (FlatType). Follows from MN_4 contrapositive: trivial holonomy ← β₁ = 0.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_5"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_6",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_6"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of monodromy composition: the monodromy map is a group homomorphism from the loop space to D_{2^n}. Follows from the composition of dihedral group elements.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_6"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_7",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/MN_7"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of TwistedType obstruction class: a TwistedType always contributes a non-zero class to H²(N(C(T')); ℤ/2ℤ) for any QuantumLift T'. Follows from MN_4 and the obstruction theory of dihedral torsors.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_MN_7"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/PT_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of PT_1: product type fiber additivity. fiberBudget(A × B) = fiberBudget(A) + fiberBudget(B). Follows from the definition of ProductType as an independent concatenation of fiber spaces.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_PT_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/PT_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of PT_2: product type partition factorisation. partition(A × B) = partition(A) ⊗ partition(B). Follows from the tensor product structure of constraint nerves over independent fiber spaces.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_PT_2"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_3",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/PT_3"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of PT_3: product type Euler characteristic additivity. χ(N(C(A × B))) = χ(N(C(A))) + χ(N(C(B))). Follows from the Künneth formula applied to the join of constraint nerves.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_PT_3"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_4",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/PT_4"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of PT_4: product type entropy additivity. S(A × B) = S(A) + S(B). Follows from PT_1 (fiber additivity) and TH_1 (S = freeCount × ln 2).",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_PT_4"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_ST_1",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/ST_1"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
      "rdfs:comment": "Proof of ST_1: sum type fiber budget maximum. fiberBudget(A + B) = max(fiberBudget(A), fiberBudget(B)). Follows from SumType requiring capacity for the larger variant.",
      "rdfs:label": "prf_ST_1"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_ST_2",
      "@type": [
        "owl:NamedIndividual",
        "https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"
      ],
      "proof:provesIdentity": {
        "@id": "https://uor.foundation/op/ST_2"
      },
      "proof:universalScope": true,
      "proof:verified": true,
